article.headline: OSU shoots 60 percent from the field
article.linkText: No. 14 Ohio St. too much for IUPUI
article.story:
COLUMBUS, Ohio (Ticker) -- Caity Matter scored 26 points as 
No. 14 Ohio State recorded its 20th straight home win with a
96-48 victory over IUPUI.

The Buckeyes shot 60 percent (18-for-30) from the field in the
first half to build a 49-21 lead heading into intermission.

Brandie Hoskins had 17 points, eight rebounds and eight assists
for Ohio State (4-0), which scored 36 off of 21 turnovers by the
Jaguars.

Starting center Jessica Davenport scored 10 points and grabbed
four rebounds for the Buckeyes.

LaToya Turner added 13 points, five rebounds and five blocks in
just 12 minutes off the bench for Ohio State, which is enjoying
its highest ranking in the polls since being ranked No. 12 in
1993.

Natalie Hendricks registered 16 points and six rebounds to lead
IUPUI (1-4), which shot just 31 percent from the floor.
